/td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else feels left out?</span><hr size=1> I don't think so, no.<br>
<br>
I think you see that we have more urgent issues because you play a wizard, and not a cleric.<br>
<br>
Many feel that we're already done, or nearly so.<br>
<br>
Many from other classes are stating that we (Wizards) were even done first, and they see any complaint that we make as pointless and ungrounded, and that we should just shut up until they finish everyone else too.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I don't know what to think about it all anymore.  <br>
<br>
I do know that, if we are done, it's not what I was expecting.  I personally was looking forward to &quot;caster balancing&quot; fixing the disparity that was created between melee's and casters since Kunark.  That disparity being the massive and continued propagation of higher damage lower delay weapons and higher ac/hp armors.<br>
<br>
Make a comparison.  Take your average melee at kunark release and compare him to your average caster at kunark release.  Then, take your average melee today, and compare him to your average caster today.  The differences are profound.<br>
<br>
I guess it's time to stop pining over the state of the game as it was 3 years ago.  It's not the same game.  We're just not going to see even the damage increase portion of change that the melee's have seen over time.  Yes, we've seen some, that I don't argue...but not nearly the increase melee's have.<br>
<br>
Prove me wrong Verant, and I'll be happy.  Prove me right and I'll be happy to...because I love my Wizard.<br>
<br>
Shizz<br>
